unittitle_ssm: Marc Crawford and Abby London Crawford Photographs
abstract_ssm: Marc Crawford, a journalist, civil rights activist and university teacher, co-authored a pictorial history of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade. His wife, Abby London Crawford, a teacher and photographer, accompanied him to veterans' reunions and related events, both in the U.S. and Spain. The collection contains Abby Crawford's photographs of these events, as well as a few related images by other photographers.
